    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for LawDog presents a clear path to offensive output, anchored by the high-ceiling matchup for **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) against Roki Sasaki. Despite Sasaki\u2019s pedigree, the current xERA of 5.52 and a favorable park factor provide **Tyler Freeman** with our top efficiency score of the day, making him an essential start. We also see strong returns from **Will Smith** (71.28) and **Jonathan Aranda** (66.50). **Jonathan Aranda** benefits specifically from an advantageous platoon matchup and a 5% boost from winds blowing out, while **Will Smith** continues to profile as an elite option in a high-leverage order spot. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a staple in our lineup (66.01), maintaining solid output despite a slight negative adjustment due to the opposing starter\u2019s skill set.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the rotation today involved the benching of **Matt Chapman** (52.74). He narrowly missed the cut behind **Luis Arraez**, whose 53.51 score was bolstered by a premium order position (#2). While **Matt Chapman** provides significant pop, the optimizer favored the efficiency of **Luis Arraez** to maintain our batting average floor. We also monitored **Gleyber Torres** (52.23), but his matchup against a high-skill arm like Garrett Crochet (2.86 xERA) rendered him a risky start compared to our active infielders. **Lawrence Butler** remains in the lineup despite a challenging platoon split (a 13% reduction) because the matchup against a struggling starter (6.23 xERA) keeps his floor high enough to justify the start in our deeper outfield configuration.\n\nManagers should monitor the status of **Will Smith**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Bryson Stott**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Lawrence Butler**, and **Cal Raleigh** as their lineups are currently pending. We are particularly cautious of the matchup for **Geraldo Perdomo**, who faces an elite arm in Kevin Gausman; while he remains in our starting nine, his efficiency is pressured by Gausman\u2019s ability to suppress production. Conversely, we are keeping **Jeremiah Jackson** (47.67) in the lineup as a marginal play to preserve roster flexibility, though he remains on a short leash if early-game performance lags behind expectations for this 5x5 Roto slate.",
